=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Level_Compensation_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright clean sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.5810
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.0017
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9262
  pitch_clarity: 3.2607
  inharmonicity: 0.0289
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -9.5937
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Level Compensation when Mixing and Panning Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Level_Compensation.html
// Tags: Level_Compensation, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
{ LinPan2.ar(DC.ar(1), Line.kr(-1, 1, 0.1)) }.plot(0.1);
// loudness seems to drop slightly when in the center
{ LinPan2.ar(PinkNoise.ar(0.2), SinOsc.kr(0.3)) }.play;
